title: The Formation of Vegetable Moulds through the Action of Worms with Observations on their Habits
creator: Charles Darwin
source: Librivox recording of a public-domain text
description: LibriVox recording of The Formation of Vegetable Moulds through the Action of Worms with Observations on their Habits, by Charles Darwin. Read by Gail Timmerman Vaughan. Charles Darwin LL.B F.R.S was the discoverer of evolution and argued the role of "natural selection" in directing the evolution of species. Darwin also had an interest in the formation of soils (moulds) that began relatively early in his life, with a paper "On the Formation of Vegetable Moulds" delivered to the Geological Society of London in 1937. Darwin's last book, The Formation of Vegetable Moulds through the Action of Worms with Observations on their Habits, was completed in 1881. (Summary by gailtv) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. Download M4B (183MB)
